  <center><h1>Samsung Research and Devolpment</h1></center>

  <b><h2><u>INTRODUCTION</u></h2></b><br>
  <p align="justify">&emsp;&emsp;Have you ever wonder, how far our lives are changed with the gadgets and technology. From Basic phones with buttons to Ultra edge bezel-less display phones with unbelievable processor speed, the era of technology has exponentially developed and changed our life style in awesome way. How is this possible? We name it as RESEARCH AND DEVOLPMENT. It is the key role for evolving technology and new approach to existing ones in our lives. The backbone of every new technology over decades is exclusively done by the only one – Research and development.  This also includes the tech giant- SAMSUNG which provides different technology and more stable software interface, to invest in Research and development with huge capital to give advancement in tech era.  Samsung research is the advanced research and development hub of Samsung Electronics which conducts new advancement in hardware’s and software to implement in the products of Samsung. </p><br>


  <p align="justify">&emsp;&emsp;Samsung’s story is an interesting one, full of both highs and lows. The hub leads the development of the future technologies with more than 10,000 researchers and developers working in overseas R&D centres. Samsung are a global innovation powerhouse that leads the trends. It is deeply invested in India — 20 years of relationships in the trade, and huge investments in local R&D. It has around 10,000 engineers working in research facilities in India and it is one of the biggest recruiters from the IITs. The hub is working in collaboration with 14 overseas R&D centres in 12 countries worldwide and 7 global AI centres to secure innovative technologies faster than anyone else and enhance its global R&D capacity. It is equally maximizing technological cooperation through active open innovation with distinguished universities, research institutes, and partner companies globally that have the world’s best technologies. Samsung has two manufacturing plants and has five R&D centres in India.
<br>
<br>
Do you know, how  the greatest tech giant of all times SAMSUNG has started ? Samsung set their foot of business in the year 1938 as a small trading company with forty employees .The  Samsung’s history is an interesting one, full of both highs and lows. Right from its founding the founder believed his new company was the start of something much bigger. The company’s name choice reflected this ambition . Samsung entered the electronics industry in the 1960's with the formation of several electronics focused divisions. The initial electronics divisions included Samsung Electronics Devices, Samsung Electro-Mechanics, Samsung Corning, and Samsung Semiconductor & Telecommunications. Samsung started their base  with initial facilities in Suwon, South Korea and japan. 
</p><br>

<p>The first electronics product ever produced by Samsung was a black and white TV in 1970. Between 1972 and 1979, Samsung began selling washing machines, changed to Samsung Petrochemical and then Samsung Heavy Industries, and by 1976, had sold its 1 millionth B&W television.

</p>

<br><p>
Will you believe now that the prototype of smart watch that we use today  was initially made by Samsung in the year 1999?
